HB 663 Original 2026 Regular Session Travis Johnson
Abstract: Modifies the membership and reduces the size of the board of commissioners of
the Delta Economic Research and Sustainability District.
Present law creates the board of commissioners (board) of the Delta Economic Research and
Sustainability District consisting of 26 members from various entities within the district and
from outside.
Proposed law eliminates the following three seats on the board:
(1) The president of the La. State University System or his designee as an ex officio
nonvoting member.
(2) The president of the La. Farm Bureau Federation or his designee as an ex officio
nonvoting member.
